annotation.TEXT: This looks to be pretty much a bullet gauntlet.
KA-BOOO- Clunk!
Okay, now that I've avoided that pit of death, this'll become the usual routine for a while, which I'll speed up.
Hey, I managed to stomp a swooper! Cool!
Slammin'!
Oh, no. My P-balloon!
Grab Mr. P-switch, and take it back to that coin arrow...

So, instead, I can think of one other path I haven't fully explored yet, and it involves me going through this autoscrolling area one more time, which I'll speed up to 8x, just to make it less boring.
Wait for it...
Okay, is this good enough?
That one worked.
Okay, forget the lava. I'll just slide-kill you!
Demo count: 10
Okay, we're back in this cave, where we can watch bob-ombs parachute through walls and all that jazz.
And, Urchins learn to fly... sort of.
What, are these ? blocks defective or something?
Alright, into the lava you go.
YES!!!
Dang it! I want to fight the boss already! Quit teasing me!
Missed again. You know what? Just forget it. I just wanna take on this boss fight now.
Okay, I think we've sacrificed enough dudes to the lava for now.
Okay, new stuff. Last time I was here, I took the lower path, which eventually led to the red switch. This time, I'll take the upper path.
I still don't know why spike tops are programmed to disappear and count as dead when they go off the screen vertically...
Awesome! Now let's hit the P-switch and see what's up there!
Okay, no more fooling around here. Just spin jump past Pokey.
Gotta pay careful attention to how they're jumping here. It looks like they jump again immediately upon hitting the ground from a high jump.
This is going to take some effort...
Also, I guess it's unusually easy to jump over this goal point using this guy! (So, maybe the yellow switch wouldn't be necessary to reach this last path.)
Oh, no. It's another one of those nutty winged platforms... Well, maybe I can bullet jump across instead.
Maybe I'll have better luck this time?
Oh, no, but now I've become... "one of them"!!!
Ha! I'm not falling for that trick again!
Wow, am I trying to kill myself here?
Yep! Now let's go get that last exit!
ACK! No fair! You're not supposed to suddenly come back down like that unless I scroll the screen again!
Wait for it...
Also, feathers. Lots of feathers.
A baseball Chuck... Well, I suppose the inside of a castle is a better place to play sports than in a blizzard (although the screwy gravity will probably be a bother).
Interesting...
Uh, what? There's nothing here?
What kind of boss fight is this? It looks like a regular room to me, so why use a boss door?
Oh, is it boss time for real now?
Wait, maybe I can still get it...
Okay, good. The Psycho-balloon has worn off.
Nuts. That might've been perfect, but I flubbed my jump attempt there!
'Kay.
Yay! Screw you winged platform!
Close call there!
Wow, did I seriously just do that?
Watch out for that lunatic fireball! But, it doesn't appear to go below a certain point, so if I stay low, and only jump when I have to, I should be fine.
Okay, gimme, gimme!
You too, spike top. Hurry up now.
Oh, for Pete's sake...
Now, can this please really be the actual boss room this time?
Gotcha!
Nuts, but it's a multi-coin block, so I get more tries.
Okay, but I'll need to somehow get a few of the coins from the upper part of the arrow, or else I'm not getting through! Maybe I can get a Chuck to help me out with that...
Nuts. I didn't mean to stomp that guy. I wanted to let him fly into the lava like this guy.
I'm going to leave the bouncing Chuck alive, just in case it turns out I need him later.
Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Repeat Offender on ZSNES!
Hmm... Let's see if I can time this right.
Oh, I just saw a Hammer Bro up there, but he's apparently heading into orbit, so... whatever!
Well, if I can't take the P-switch with me into that area, I may as well use it here for some coins.
So, let me guess. That was exit number four, right?
And two dings means it's done!
Oh, that's interesting. I exactly doubled my bonus stars there.
YAAAHHH!!! Stupid fake floor! Ooh, treasure!
So, I guess we're in castle town, complete with levitating Lava Lotuses.
Let's try that again, and make sure not to fall into that pit again like an idiot!
So, do we get an end credits sequence now?
Well, the swoopers aren't working right, and as for Blargg...
Alright, Chuck, can you bounce way over here for me please?
Uh, oh...
Not really much to talk about here. Maybe I should've sped this part up?
Demo count: 12
Also, I'm digging the left wall's graphics. How come the right wall doesn't look like that as well?
Well, I had a better idea (which I've since forgotten), but that works too I guess.
Demo count: 11
Oh, man. More Pokeys, and they've got more coverage than [insert cellphone company name of your choice here]. I'd better wait until at least one of them falls into the pit.
AAAHHH... Nuts.
And now we have a Pokey. He appears to be affected in a similar way to the others here.
Demo count: 13
Alright, nuts to you all. I'm just going to rush through most of this.
Okay, I think I want to land now...
Ooh, a risky multi-coin block. I remember a couple of those in the original SMB, and I would often get blasted while trying to empty them out back in the day.
I can't believe it! This stupid freaking shell killed my Chuck!
Uh, oh. Don't worry Chuck! I'll save you with the power of L and R!
KA-BOOOOM!!!
Now, I know there's a path just to the right I haven't explored yet, but since it apparently required all four switches to be hit, I'm going to save it for last.
Ooh, treasure! Screw the boss, I want treasure!
Huh? Why didn't he die?
Cheap Cheep-Cheep!
As usual, that koopa keels over and I grab my habitual mushroom here.
Come on. All of you go into the lava.
And, somewhere along the way, I hit all of the remaining switch palaces, as well as exit number 5. Now, let's search for those last two exits!
Oh, come on! How did I let that mushroom get away! Well, I bet this isn't the boss room anyway.
A hidden 1-up? I went through all that work for just a 1-up?! That's it, I'm out of here!
Ah, but it is, finally!
Um, where do I go from here?
No, we just return to the title screen with an "X" under the number 6, which means I found every exit! ...I think.
The rest of this raft ride is pretty uneventful.
Shattering transition to back here again.
Oh, there's actually cave music here.
Aw, it's a door, not a pipe. That means I can't bring my P-switch with me.
I guess I was all too eager there...
GAAAAAMMME!!!
However, I'm not quite done yet. I want to see what's above the first coin arrow at the beginning of the level.
Okay, now beyond goal number one, with all four switches hit, I can now access one last path over here.
Here, Chucky, Chucky... Over here please!
Last time, on Repeat Offender...
I better get running speed just to make sure I make this jump.
Ah, a Sumo Brother. How does he function in this wacky gravitational field?
Huh. I guess I can sometimes kick something I'm holding to the right...
But, first. This shell must die! I was thinking of spin jumping on it, but I have a better idea!
Whoa! Now that was close!
Wow, even Charlie-man here is fading into obscurity.
Ooh, the goal!
Well, I guess I can enlist the help of the bouncing Chuck that I let live earlier.
Ooh, I got the block-kill timing right on that one!
Collect a few coins from the middle, but leave a couple on the bottom, because I intend to use the P-switch here later.
I think grabbing the mushroom there affected my jump height coming out of the water, preventing me from getting over the bullet cannon on the first attempt.
If I missed anything important, let me know, but otherwise, I think I'm done!
No, unless these Ninji ghosts count as the boss, but I doubt it.
Well, that guy casually sacrificed himself...
Let me just take a quick look around first...
